urons. Written in a fun, easy-to-comprehend style and filled with illuminating analogies, Our Intelligent Bodies also brings readers up to date on cutting-edge research into the wonders of human physiology. It will give you a new appreciation for the smart decisions our bodies are making when our brains aren’t paying attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHuman physiology. 0aOrgans (Anatomy). 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aHealth, Medicine, boby, intelligent bodies, Science, Life Sciences, Human Anatomy, Physiology, fitness, Vision, Hearing, Cochlea, Proprioception, Balance, Acid Base, pH Regulation, Cardiovascular, Hemodynamics, Respiration, Kidneys, Body Water, Gut, Nutrient, Nutrient Flow, Gary F. Merrill, pulmonary system, oxygen levels, second brain, neurons, physiological structures.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081359855040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813598550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813598550/original  a978-3-11-069033-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles